# D365 F&O Scenario Router

Microsoft source: [Extend F&O apps](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/guidance/implementation-guide/extend-your-solution-guidance-product-fo)

Use this when the task type is unclear. Pick the row that matches your scenario, then follow the linked domain rule.

| Scenario | Recommended approach | Avoid | Domain rule / skill |
|----------|---------------------|-------|---------------------|
| Add field/index to standard table | Table extension + indexes in extension | Overlayering base table; redundant copy table | `xpp-fno-data-access` / `xpp-fno-data` |
| Validate before save | CoC on `validateWrite` / `validateInsert` (table or form DS) | Overlay; logic only in form with no CoC | `xpp-fno-extensibility` |
| Run logic after save | CoC on `insert`/`update` if wrappable; else **Pre/Post event** (additive) | `doInsert`/`doUpdate`; unconditional `EventHandlerResult` | `xpp-fno-extensibility` |
| Replace calculation/strategy | `[Replaceable]` + CoC, or SysExtension plug-in | Copy-paste entire standard method | `xpp-fno-extensible-design` |
| Show field on standard form | Form extension (control) + label | Overlayer base form; hardcoded caption | `xpp-fno-forms-ui` |
| New periodic export/process | **SysOperationServiceController** + contract/service | New `RunBaseBatch` for greenfield code | `xpp-fno-data-access` + business-logic skill |
| Bulk update many rows | `update_recordset` / chunked TTS | Row-by-row `while select` + `update()` in one TTS | `xpp-fno-data-access` |
| Expose data to integration | Built-in entity if sufficient; custom entity for high volume | Many one-off OData endpoints | `xpp-fno-security` + `xpp-fno-data` |
| New menu item / action | Privilege → duty → role (least privilege) | Unsecured menu item; edit standard role | `xpp-fno-security` |
| Unit test new logic | `SysTestCase` + ATL + AutoRollback | Tests on production; demo data dependency | `xpp-fno-testing` |
| Pre-release / PR | BP zero, compatibility checker, CAR, SysTest | Shipping without entry-point security | `/xpp-fno-code-review` |
| No extension point exists | Log **LCS extensibility request** early | Overlayering; fork standard code | `xpp-fno-core` |

## Extension technique decision (quick)

1. Metadata only (field, control, property)? → **Extension artifact**
2. Wrappable method exists? → **CoC** (`next` at first level)
3. Framework Pre/Post event? → **Event handler** (additive)
4. Factory / SysExtension? → **Plug-in** (Liskov-safe)
5. None? → **LCS request** — do not overlay

## Quality gates by scenario

| Scenario | Minimum before merge |
|----------|----------------------|
| Any metadata change | Best practice check; compatibility checker vs baseline |
| Any new entry point | Privilege mapping verified in security model |
| Performance-sensitive path | Trace Parser on hot scenario |
| Batch/job change | Parameter versioning if pack/unpack changed |
| All custom code | SysTest for new/changed business rules |

Hub skill: `xpp-fno-development`. Full PR checklist: `/xpp-fno-code-review`.
